# 📱 Mobile System Scan — `scheduling_mobile`

> **Scanned:** April 23, 2026  
> **Project:** Faculty Dashboard — NORSU Scheduling System Mobile App  
> **Framework:** Flutter 3.x (Dart SDK ^3.11.0)  
> **State Mgmt:** Riverpod (`flutter_riverpod`) + legacy `ChangeNotifier`  

---

## 1. Project Overview

| Attribute | Value |
|---|---|
| Package name | `scheduling_mobile` |
| Version | `1.0.0+1` |
| Min SDK | `^3.11.0` |
| Font | Outfit (bundled), Poppins (Google Fonts — runtime) |
| Theme mode | Light only (`ThemeMode.light`) |
| Target platforms | Android, iOS, Web |

### Purpose
A faculty-facing mobile companion to a Symfony-based scheduling backend. Faculty members log in, view their dashboard & class schedule, manage notifications, submit schedule-change requests, and complete their profile.

---

## 2. Dependency Summary

| Package | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `provider` | ^6.1.2 | Listed but **not actually used** — Riverpod is the real state manager |
| `flutter_riverpod` | (in lock) | Actual state management |
| `http` | ^1.2.1 | REST API calls |
| `flutter_secure_storage` | ^9.2.2 | Token & credential storage |
| `intl` | ^0.19.0 | Date/time formatting |
| `cupertino_icons` | ^1.0.8 | iOS-style icons |
| `google_fonts` | (in lock) | Runtime font loading (Poppins) |
| `flutter_local_notifications` | (in lock) | Class reminder notifications |
| `timezone` | (in lock) | Timezone-aware scheduling |

> [!WARNING]
> `google_fonts` runtime fetching is **disabled** (`allowRuntimeFetching = false`) in [main.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/main.dart#L26), yet `LoginScreen` uses `GoogleFonts.poppins()` everywhere — this will silently fall back to the default font.

> [!WARNING]
> `provider` package is in `pubspec.yaml` but the app exclusively uses `flutter_riverpod`. This is dead weight.

