## 5. 🚨 Critical Issues Found

### 5.1 Empty Files That Are Imported

These files are **empty (0 bytes)** but imported by other code, causing **compile-time failures**:

| Empty File | Imported By | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| `config/api_config.dart` | `services/api_service.dart` → `ApiConfig.baseUrl` | ❌ **Build will fail** — `ApiConfig` class doesn't exist |
| `services/auth_service.dart` | `providers/auth_provider.dart` → `AuthService()` | ❌ **Build will fail** — `AuthService` class doesn't exist |
| `models/user.dart` | `providers/auth_provider.dart` → `User` type | ❌ **Build will fail** — `User` class doesn't exist |
| `models/schedule.dart` | (potentially imported) | ⚠️ Empty placeholder |
| `config/app_theme.dart` | (not imported) | ⚠️ Dead file |
| `widgets/schedule_card.dart` | (not imported) | ⚠️ Dead file |

> [!CAUTION]
> The combination of empty `auth_service.dart`, `user.dart`, and `api_config.dart` means the app **cannot compile** as-is. These are foundational files that core providers depend on.

### 5.2 Dual State Management Conflict

The [auth_provider.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/providers/auth_provider.dart) uses `ChangeNotifier` (Provider pattern):
```dart
class AuthProvider extends ChangeNotifier { ... }
```

But **every screen** uses it as a Riverpod provider with `ref.watch(authProvider)` and `ref.read(authProvider.notifier)`, expecting `AuthState` and `AuthNotifier` types that **don't exist** in the current file.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There must be a **different version** of `auth_provider.dart` that defines Riverpod's `StateNotifierProvider<AuthNotifier, AuthState>`. The current file is the **wrong implementation** — it's a `ChangeNotifier`-based provider that doesn't match how screens consume it.

### 5.3 ApiService Constructor Mismatch

- [api_provider.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/providers/api_provider.dart#L49) calls `ApiService(baseUrl: baseUrl)`
- [api_service.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/services/api_service.dart#L8) defines `factory ApiService() => _instance` — **no `baseUrl` parameter**

Additionally, providers call methods like `getFacultyDashboard()`, `getFacultySchedule()`, `getNotifications()`, `hasToken`, `getColleges()`, `getDepartments()`, `listScheduleChangeRequests()`, `listRooms()`, `checkScheduleChangeConflict()`, `cancelScheduleChangeRequest()`, etc. — **none of these exist** in the current `api_service.dart`.

> [!CAUTION]
> The `ApiService` has only generic `get()/post()/put()/delete()` methods. All domain-specific methods are **missing**.

### 5.4 Duplicate Model Definitions

[faculty_models.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/models/faculty_models.dart) duplicates classes from multiple other model files:

| Class | Also defined in |
|---|---|
| `UserProfile` | `user_model.dart` (with extra `middleName`, `otherDesignation`, `toJson()`) |
| `Department` | `user_model.dart`, `schedule_change_request_model.dart` |
| `College` | `user_model.dart` |
| `DashboardData` | `dashboard_model.dart` (with `toJson()`) |
| `DashboardStats` | `dashboard_model.dart` (with `toJson()`) |
| `AcademicYear` | `dashboard_model.dart` (with `toJson()`) |
| `ScheduleItem` | `dashboard_model.dart` (with `timeStatus`, `toJson()`) |
| `Subject` | `dashboard_model.dart` (with `toJson()`) |
| `Room` | `dashboard_model.dart` (with `toJson()`) |
| `NotificationItem` | `notification_model.dart` (much more robust parsing) |

The duplicates in `faculty_models.dart` are **less featured** (missing `toJson()`, `timeStatus`, `copyWith()`, etc.). This will cause ambiguous import errors.

### 5.5 `auth_provider.dart` Line 1 Syntax Error

```dart
-import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
```

Line 1 has a leading `-` character — this is a **syntax error** that will prevent compilation.

---

## 6. ⚠️ Non-Critical Issues

### 6.1 Duplicate AppColors Classes

Two separate `AppColors` classes exist with **different color palettes**:

| File | Primary Color | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| [app/configs/theme.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/app/configs/theme.dart) | `#465FFF` (blue) | **Used by the app** — main design system |
| [app/configs/colors.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/app/configs/colors.dart) | `#7D50F0` (purple) | ⚠️ Unused legacy — different values |

### 6.2 Login Screen Style Mismatch

[login_screen.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/screens/login_screen.dart) uses:
- `GoogleFonts.poppins()` (can't load at runtime since fetching is disabled)
- Green color scheme (`#4CAF50`) instead of the app's blue theme (`#465FFF`)
- Its own input decoration, **ignoring** the app theme

Meanwhile, [signin_page.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/ui/auth/screens/signin_page.dart) uses the proper design system (`auth_constants.dart` → `AppColors`). These are **two competing login screens**.

### 6.3 Unused Legacy Data Models

`lib/data/gallery_model.dart` and `lib/data/post_model.dart` appear to be leftover from a starter template and have nothing to do with scheduling.

### 6.4 Hardcoded API URL in Constants

[utils/constants.dart](file:///c:/Users/HVergara/scheduling_mobile/lib/utils/constants.dart#L5) has `const String apiBaseUrl = 'http://localhost:8000/api'` while `api_provider.dart` has platform-aware URL resolution. The constant is likely unused but could cause confusion.

### 6.5 No `.env` File

Only `.env.example` exists — no actual `.env` file for runtime configuration.

